SIMPLE: humming
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Humming
<hw>Hum"ming</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Emitting a murmuring
sound; droning; murmuring; buzzing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Humming</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Humming
<hw>Hum"ming</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sound like that made by bees; a
low, murmuring sound; a hum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hummingale</b></col>, <cd>lively or strong ale.</cd>
<au>Dryden.</au> -- <col><b>Humming-bird moth</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a hawk moth. See <cref>Hawk moth</cref>, under
<er>Hawk</er>, the bird.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>humming bird</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>hummingbird</ent>⟦br⟧
